{"origin":17238,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Sahaba: Companions had fun, yet showed courage","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Bakr ibn Abdullah reported: The companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would throw melons at each other for fun, but when it came to the truth, they would be real men. Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 261 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0628\u064e\u0643\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11892,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/29\/beloved-jihad-word-haqq-justice\/","url_meta":{"origin":17238,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Jihad: Most beloved jihad speaking justice to oppressors","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 29, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was asked, \u201cWhich jihad\u00a0is most beloved to Allah?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cA word of truth before a tyrannical leader.\u201d Source: al-Sunan al-Kubra\u0301 lil-Bayhaqi\u0304\u00a020185 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064f\u0626\u0650\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":41396,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/10\/05\/speak-no-evil\/","url_meta":{"origin":17238,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Silence: Allah has mercy on those who speak no evil","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Khalid ibn Abi \u2018Imran reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would hold his tongue for a long time. Then, the Prophet said, \u201cI fear for you because of this. May Allah have mercy on a servant who speaks goodness and is rewarded, or he refrains from speaking\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24509,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/03\/10\/wisdom-abu-dharr\/","url_meta":{"origin":17238,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hikmah: The Prophet\u2019s wise advice for Abu Dharr","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 10, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, instruct me.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cI advise you to fear Allah Almighty, for it will beautify all of your affairs.\u201d I said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cYou must recite the Quran and remember\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"a